checkpoint.name: Delivery tray in case of emergency
Ambu bag for babies(240 ml) with both pre & term mask (size 0,1)
Color coded bags for disposal of biomedical waste
Cold storage for Inj. Oxytocin at the point of use
Functional oxygen cylinder (with wrench) with new born mask
Curtain in labor room to ensure privacy to woman
There is one fan for each labor table
Each labor table has 1 shadow less light
Labor room has air-conditioning/ exhaust ventilation
Labor room has at least 2 ceiling mounted lights
Entry to the labor room is not direct
Window and door glass are frosted
Each labor table has provision for cover on three sides (by screens or curtains)
Windows have curtains of light color
Washroom has functional hand washing area for users
Washroom has direct access from the labor room
There is a dirty utility area with direct access from labor room

Availability of adequate number of labor tables as per delivery load
 (Please refer to details of standards for adequate number as per delivery load)
All labor tables are clean, non-broken, and non-rusted
Newborn corner has free space on three sides
Newborn corner is in direct access to the labor tables (no obstruction)
Two labor tables have adequate space between them (preferably 6 feet)

Nursing station is located in a place from where nurses can observe clients without any
 interruptions

Floor of the labor room is constructed of anti-skid vitrified tiles/ natural stone/ equivalent,
 with seamless joints, preferably of white/ ivory color

Walls of labor room have wall tiles of white color with seamless joints extending up to the
 height of door of the room
All windows and doors are in proper condition
Station has uniteruppted supply of running water
Assesses uterine tone and bleeding per vaginum regularly
Calls for help /asistance, while continue uterine message
Two pre warmed clean towels are available
If breathing is normal, dries the baby immediately using first towel and then wraps in second warm towel
Delivers the baby on mother’s abdomen
Initiates breast feeding within one hour of birth
Performs delayed cord clamping and cutting
Switches radiant warmer ‘on’ 30 min before childbirth
Designated new born corner is present
Ensures functional items for newborn care and resuscitation
Ensures availability of pre-filled oxytocin syringe
Ensures required number of sterile/HLD delivery tray is available (2 trays per labor table),
Counsels on exclusive breast feeding to mother at discharge
Counsels on danger signs to mother at time of discharge
Counsels on post partum family planning to mother at discharge
Takes obstetric, medical and surgical history
Assesses gestational age through either LMP or Fundal height or USG (if available)
Functional doppler/fetoscope/stethoscope at point of use is available
Records fetal heart rate at admission
Functional BP instrument and stethoscope at point of use is available
Records mother' s temperature at admission
Functional thermometer at point of use is available
Facilitates thermal management including kangaroo mother care

Administers Injn Oxytocin 10 I.U. IM/IV within one minute of delivery of baby
Checks placenta and membranes for completeness before discarding
Palpates mothers abdomen to rule out second baby

Checks for test results or recommends testing if not done

ART center is available in facility
Provides Nevirapine to (HIV seropositive) pregnant woman and refers her to ARTC after delivery
Conducts PV examination only as indicated (4 hourly or based) on clinical indication
Cleans the perineum appropriately before conducting PV examination
Soap and running water is available
Wears gloves on both the hands with correct technique
Records the finding of PV examination (in Case sheet/Partograph during active phase of labour)
Initiates Partograph plotting once the Cx dilation is >=4 cm
Partographs in labor room are available
Provider interprets partograph correctly and adjusts care according to findings
Counsels mother on importance of exclusive and on demand breast feeding

Functional BP instrument and stethoscope at point of use is available
Identifies danger signs or presence of convulsions
MgSO4 in labor room (atleast 20 ampoules) is available
Ensures specialist attention for care of mother and newborn
Curtain in labor room to ensure privacy to woman are available
Treats woman and her companion cordially and respectfully (RMC), ensures privacy and confidentiality to woman during her stay
Encourages the presence of birth companion during labour
Explains important care activities to mother and her companion during her stay (for mother and baby)
Explains danger signs to mother and her companion during her stay (for mother and baby)
Functional BP instrument and stethoscope at point of use is available

Looks for signs of infection in baby

Instruments and gloves after is decontaminated after each use using chlorine soln/Gluteraldehyde (Gluteraldehyde for instruments)
Bleaching powder/ Sodium hypochlorite soln/Gluteraldehyde is available
Assess the appropriateness of administration of antibiotics before discharge.
Assess the appropriateness of administration of antibiotics at admission.
